data.name: Label3.Text
data.value:
This page is used to configure the Remote Lab System User Interface for a particular host computer. This tab should only be used by professors and lab assistants, not by students.
Note to Students: If you change the name of the COM port, you will not be able to complete your experiment and get credit for your lab assignment. Please do not alter this page in any way. Thank you.
Note to Professors and Lab Assistants: The first time you plug in the RLS to a new host computer, open the Device Manager from the Start menu. Look under the Ports dropdown section and identify which COM port the RLS is attached to. Edit Line 5 of the file Form1.vb so that the default COM port matches the COM port showing in the Device Manager. The RLS should perform as expected as long as the USB plug remains connected to the same computer.
For testing purposes, you can temporarily change the COM port using this page (for example, if you want to test the system using your personal computer and you don't want to bother to change the code). Enter the name of the COM port in this box (for example, COM4) and click "Submit." DO NOT type Enter; you must click the "Submit" button instead. You will have to repeat this process each time you load the user interface program.
